org.knime.core.node.workflow

Interface NodeContainerParent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SubNodeContainer, WorkflowManager

    public interface NodeContainerParent
    Interface used by embedded WorkflowManager instances to invoke actions on the parent item. The parent item is a WorkflowManager for meta nodes or projects. It is a SubNodeContainer for the instance that is used inside a sub node.

    None of the methods are meant be public API.

    Since:
    2.10
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

      • canResetContainedNodes

        boolean canResetContainedNodes()
        If a contained node contained (independent of its connections). Generally true but subnodes disallow node reset if there are downstream executing nodes.
        Returns:
        that property.

      • canConfigureNodes

        boolean canConfigureNodes()
        May return false for nodes contained in subnodes, which cannot be configured until all data is available to the subnode. Used to ensure the user doesn't execute nodes in a subnode unless all data is available. For ordinary workflows/meta nodes it always returns true.
        Returns:
        that property

      • getReentrantLockInstance

        ReentrantLock getReentrantLockInstance()
        Returns:
        the ReentrantLock underlying the WorkflowLock instance used by this NC parent.

      • lock

        WorkflowLock lock()
        Locks and returns the WorkflowLock associated with this workflow. This should always be used in a try-with-resources statement: 
         try (WorkflowLock lock = lock()) {
    ...
 }
        Returns:
        The workflow lock instance, freshly locked (see ReentrantLock.lock().

      • isLockedByCurrentThread

        boolean isLockedByCurrentThread()
        Returns:
        true if the calling thread has acquired the workflow lock either via lock() or by locking the ReentrantLock. Mainly used for assertions.

      • isWriteProtected

        boolean isWriteProtected()
        Is this workflow represents a linked meta node (locked for edit). This flag is only a hint for the UI -- non of the add/remove operations will read this flag.
        Returns:
        Whether edit operations are not permitted.

      • getCipherFileName

        String getCipherFileName(String fileName)
        Returns the argument string unless this workflow or any of the parent wfms is encrypted. Then it appends ".encrypted" to the argument.
        Parameters:
        fileName - Suggest file name
        Returns:
        fileName, possibly appended with ".encrypted".
        No public API: not to be referenced by clients
        This method is not intended to be referenced by clients.
